(firstQuint)Oral Steroids Before Pulmonary Vein Isolation to Improve Outcomes.

 The purpose of this study is: 1.

 To assess the efficacy of oral prednisone in improving the outcomes of pulmonary vein isolation with radiofrequency ablation.

 2.

 To measure the inflammatory cytokine (TNF-, IL-1, IL-6, IL-8) response to radiofrequency ablation for atrial fibrillation with or without prior prednisone treatment.

